OL,3,CTime for clarity regarding future of
OL,4,CFreeview
OL,6,FThe question over Freeview's long-term
OL,7,Ffuture is based on two issues:
OL,8,Fquestions over whether frequencies
OL,9,Fshould be turned over to other uses `
OL,10,Fsuch as improving mobile broadband `
OL,11,Fand the support of the broadcasters
OL,12,Ffor Freely.
OL,14,FFreely is dubbed the successor to
OL,15,FFreeview ` but would it not be better
OL,16,Fto describe it as an upgrade?
OL,18,FIt will be interesting to see how much
OL,19,Fdemand there actually is for Freely
OL,20,Fsets. At present set-top boxes are
OL,21,Funavailable.
OL,1,W~+$ hw1~{4~k4 ~shw1~sj7}         G2/7
