OL,3,CTime for clarity regarding future of
OL,4,CFreeview
OL,6,FHowever the idea of switching off
OL,7,FFreeview and actually replacing it
OL,8,Fwith Freely depends on one crucial
OL,9,Ffactor. Every home would need access
OL,10,Fto fast, reliable, unmetered internet
OL,11,Faccess.
OL,13,FAnd even if that access existed, would
OL,14,Fsome people ` especially those who are
OL,15,Fvulnerable and some older people `
OL,16,Factually want it?
OL,18,FAdvances in consumer technology and
OL,19,Fchanging behaviour do not in
OL,20,Fthemselves justify doing anything
OL,21,Fwhich leaves some people behind.
OL,1,W~+$ hw1~{4~k4 ~shw1~sj7}         G3/7
